<TITLE> 'Miscreant' killed in shootout with RAB in Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 6 (bdnews24.com)An alleged miscreant was killed early on Friday near Ibrahimpur market in the capital in a so-called gunfight with RAB. Kafrul police chief Delwar Ahmed claimed that Amir Ali, 34, was a close associate of 'Taj', a top terror of Mirpur area. Major Sarwar of RAB-4 told bdnews24.com they were conducting a raid beside Ibrahimpur market in the early hours on Friday when they challenged 'a group of terrorists'. "During the raid, the miscreants fired at RAB members and as they retaliated, Amir Ali was hit by a bullet." Amir was later admitted to Dhaka Medical College and Hospital where he died from the wounds, Delwar said. He said that Amir had quite a few cases filed against him. bdnews24
